 The SAVF Silverdays old age home in Waterval Boven is running very low on suppplies. According to Silverdays’ matron, Gail Fish, the home is in urgent need of groceries, veggies, prepaid electricity as well as medical supplies,  “as our subsidies are extremely late and we are struggling right now to cope.” ALSO READ: Silwerdae het steeds ‘n voedseltekort “Please can all our wonderful friends out there who helped us in the past with blessing our home reach out once again in this time of need,” Fish pleaded and added that any donations are welcome. Lowvelder reported on the problem before. The home has been struggling with food since 2017. ALSO READ: Silwerdae Ouetehuis verkeer steeds in nood 